reviews_data.review_text: Best coffe shop in the area. Friendly service and awesome coffee. Delicious pastries.
Fresh made coffee. The best around town!!! Highly recommend. Excellent customer service. Very friendly staff. Plenty of setting. Great for a meeting or work from home atmosphere.
Service was excellent, coffee is amazing. I tried a spinach feta croissant which was amazing and a mocha latte. Abet is so kind and welcoming.
6 star service, delicious coffee and treats. Will be going back again and again.

Yes. It's different. Yes, Joe (his real name is Abed pronounced ah-bed and we should call him that) works very hard to communicate. But those are good things, not bad!

Don't be scared of the music, the difference in the drinks from Starbucks. Lean into it. Give something a try. You'll be back if you do.

+1 for the bee bites. haven't had them this good in a long while.

6/5 stars!!! Joe is a little hard with English but once the barrier is crossed he is very friendly and his cofeee is easily the best in charlotte and surrounding areas!!!! Hands down the best cofeee barista I have ever met

The best coffee I've had in a very long time! I came in to do some paperwork on my computer sat down and before I knew it I had this lovely presentation for my coffee which was outstanding, I was extremely pleasantly surprised when I took my first sip. It was very pretty but I was not expecting the flavor to be so spot on. I honestly can't remember the last time  I have  had coffee this good and I love coffee. The girl who made it was incredibly polite and kind. The service was excellent. It was a quiet atmosphere. I will definitely be back. I have a huge comfortable couch where you can sit at a table, but it's a big open space and it doesn't feel cramped or overcrowded. This is my second time there. I also did have the coffee cake milk cake which was again out of this world. I asked that they had tiramisu and she recommended the coffee cake because they did not and I was not disappointed at all. I found a new dessert that I absolutely love. I did notice that the girl who works there skipped over the part where I'm allowed to tip her on the computer system I had to ask her for her copy of the receipt so I could write down her tip on there & it. She was just going to give me my receipt and nowhere to tip.  and she did the same thing when my mom went to pay her as well because my mom came and met me and I didn't know what coffee she wanted two separate transactions. So if you go and you get this wonderful young lady I recommend tipping her and maybe doing it in cash to make sure that she is able to get her to because I don't think she gets paid enough.  I know when Mount Holly finds out about this gem it'll get crowded and not be a quiet place to work anymore but I'll still go back for the coffee! I cannot express enough that I can't remember the last time that I have had coffee that tasted this good!
The coffee and the pastries are delicious. The exceptional customer service of the friendly staff added to the great experience. This is a must visit place in Mount Holly.

Every time we go, the owner Yusuf is so nice. His coffees and baked goods are wonderful. Now that it's getting colder we'll have to drop by to try his hot drinks. We've loved his caramel frappes, match frappes with almond milk, cinnamon rolls, and another baked good called Sabaya with flaky baklava crust but topped with honey and sesame seeds. The shop is always clean and comfortable, we love visiting.
Great service and Amazing drinks.
Have not gone yet will update review once I go. Just wondering why you don't open til 9am? 7-8am seems more ideal as people usually drink coffee really early like otw to work(before 8am).

Absolutely phenomenal! The atmosphere was warm and inviting and the service was amazing. They have Something for everyone as well. If you like Middle Eastern coffee or want to try it they have a lot to pick from and they also have regular lattes, macchiatos, etc. If you're a fall drink lover like I am I highly recommend the pumpkin pie latte! Easily the best fall drink I've had. I will definitely be going back!

The abest
cafe in Charlotte

You want to taste what real coffee taste like? Come to this place! You'll thank me later. I had a whole mind blowing history lesson when it comes to coffee and I'm glad I went on that journey. I'll never go to a regular coffee place again. Coffee originated from Yemen which makes Coffee Origins a gem in the coffee world. This is a must if you are a coffee person!

They also have Yemeni pastries that deliciously hit the spot along with the type and flavor coffee you're having. Went to their grand opening today. Customer for life now.

Outstanding coffee and service.  There is plenty of room to enjoy your coffee. Lots of taste treats to enjoy as well (cheesecakes, croissants, and other pastries).

Just opened and worth your visit.
What an incredible staff with amazing pastries! If you're in the area, come in!

Came in randomly and found a new favorite coffee spot! Abed was so amazing, greeted us upon arrival, seated us before taking our order and then served us. The couches were also really groovy. 13/10 recommend! Thank you Abed Jordan

Fantastic! A great addition to the area. A wonderful & unique selection of international coffees/teas and such warm & friendly service. A great spot to come solo, meet up with friends or have a nice, informal meeting.

The place was closed,  when on Google Maps clearly
Showed it was  open
Amazing flavorful pistachio latte  the desserts and cheesecakes looked so good, can't wait to try next time.

Love the business concept for the area. They should go to apt offices, banks, other businesses etc w flyers. We all will strongly support it. Family visited a eatery like this in a small town in Virginia doing well--very clean, simple. If i were the owner i would incorporate a "few" very simple small sandwiches (no more than 3/4 diff types) like grilled cheese, chicken salad croissants, egg salad & basic ham/turkey-lettuce & tomato-edges cut off, mini banana nut muffins, thats it to add to the different coffees. They can shorten the other items on t menu to one type of cake & cheesecake slices and/or sweet potato pie. Simple.. To keep the focus on coffees
New coffee shop in Mt Holly, love their iced Spanish latte. Good strong flavor. The owner seems very friendly. It's very quiet. I love it, will be a regular customer here.

What a nice surprise -- in Mount Holly. My first time to enjoy cardamom coffee! The pastry is delicious -- but pricey. Nice atmosphere. I am enjoying the Arabic music. When there are finishing touches on the construction and decor, I will confidently give a 5 star rating.
I stop by today and tried the adeni karak chai and it was so amazing and thy have a lot of teas,coffees opinions and pastries I can't to go back and try some other menu items
The Pistachio Latte is a must try and I definitely will be back
They have so many good options, and a calming atmosphere. I'll be making more stops here for sure!
Got an iced pistachio latte today, it was amazing! I'd definitely recommend coming here.

So glad I stopped here today. Such a cute place. Very middle eastern vibe and so many different coffee/teas and desserts choose from. I tried the Yemen tea and loved it! Cheese cake was delicious to. Very fresh. Also very sweet/friendly staff. Will definitely be back!
Do you have a good coughing good customer service you have to try it
Is the best cafe the best cake the best everything?

Such a refreshing change for typical coffee flavors, in a welcoming and open space. Great service. Really delicious coffee and desserts. Thrilled to have this new spot in Mt. Holly. Cardamom belongs with coffee!!!
I was really excited to try this place but no one was there when I went at 8am. I tried calling to be sure but no one answered. Bummer.

The coffee is absolutely delicious and the pastries are delightful. I got the Sana'ani (hot) and my wife got the Yemeni latte, both served quickly and tasted great.

The barista was very helpful with picking out what I would like, and treated us very kindly. Excited to come back!

The drinks and food are really good, but of the 3 times I've been during their open hours I've only been able to experience once. The other two times I will go and the smoke shop next door just says the owner didn't come in that day and doesn't know why. If yoy do happen to catch it open it's great but I definitely wouldn't rely on it to be open and have a backup plan.
Chill environment  with amazing drinks, coffee is rich and full flavored and their refreshers have a depth of flavor known to no other establishments in the area

I've been eyeing this place for a few weeks wondering if they were open. Finally saw this morning the we are open sign. I told my husband we had to check it out. Upon walking in it is spacious and we were greeted. I asked the gentleman when they opened.he said right now it is just a soft open as they still need to decorate and still have pastries and supplies they are having come in. The menu looks Devine. I got the white chocolate mocha iced and a chai tea. Both were delicious. I look forward to their grand opening. I look forward to trying all their things. Give them a try

This shop is wonderful. They have all types of Middle Eastern coffee plus traditional espresso drinks. They were very patient and answered my many questions. The coffee is delicious and reasonably priced.  I will definitely go back.
Lovely drinks! Got the hibiscus blackberry ice tea and the pink drink. Both were amazing!! The host at the counter was super welcoming. Highly recommend!
This place coffee is so amazing everybody should try it and the service is very good
This place is awesome the staff is amazing the tea is very good and also sweets they have amazing

Amazing experience.  The staff was super kind and willing to answer any questions I had.  The coffees offered a incredible and unique with flavors I have not had before.  I also enjoyed the coffee cake they had as well.

This place can broaden your horizons when it comes to coffee- or you can get the same old thing, if you prefer.

They have many different styles of coffee that you may not have experienced!

This break opened shop is a one of a kind gem- guaranteed to give you a unique and pleasant experience!

I got a Mufuaar- which was very good! I loved the cardamom.
I can't wait to go back and try some other drinks!

They're still building out the location, but there is a lot of seating and the service was great- very friendly and willing to provide recommendations.

If you're not familiar with the styles of drink- I recommend ordering a large, as some of the styles of drink have the spices or coffee grounds in it- making the bottom of the drink grainy.
Also they often come out very hot - careful!

I highly recommend you give this new, unique coffee shop a try. I know I will certainly be back!

Very friendly and respectful young men. They went out of their way to explain the selections they have available. Very clean and friendly atmosphere.

Welcome to the neighborhood guys!

Went here for the first time yesterday. We were greeted promptly and order three different beverages.  Then they gave us one on the house for my little 7 year old. All 4 beverages were delicious!  Highly recommend.  They should have pastries soon, and will be doing more decorating.
